textAfterTable: Event Detail Information Event Detail Information 3-Legged Tale Date Apr 22, 2013 Time 7:00 pm   Location Sangamon Auditorium, UIS Sponsor News Channel 20; 104.5 WFMB; 99.7 KISSFM Phone 217-206-6160 Event type Family Views 7011 "3-Legged Tale" by Theatre de l'CEil is a philosophical story without words, a poetic reflection on the cycle of life, of time that passes and that changes us, on life which is in constant rebirth, like grass that grows again after a field fire or flowers that appear after the snow.   The story tells of a pilfering squirrel that discovers a camera on a tripod in a trash pile in the woods. When a butterfly lands on the camera it suddenly springs to life, venturing forth to explore and interact with the new world around it. link for robots only
